<HEAD>Returns Stolen Loot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KEENE, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A thief apparently troubled by a guilty conscience returned $ 4,500 to a bank after taking the money to buy Christmas gifts, police said. Fleet Bank-N.H. reported this week that two bags containing the cash and checks were missing. The next day, the bank received a large envelope in the mail containing the cash bags, the cash and a note saying the sender had found the bags outside the post offce, opened them and decided to return them. Police said the package was traced to a 19-year-old <PERSON> Keene </PERSON> man, who was to have put the money in a night deposit box for his employer. The business has decided not to press charges, police said.
