<HEAD>How Canada's Worst Mass Murder Unfolded</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Canada-Shooting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTREAL (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The first call from the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Montreal </ORGANIZATION> came into the city's emergency 911 phone line in late afternoon. `` There is a hostage-taking, there is gunfire and there are lots of people wounded,'' police quoted the caller as saying. It was the beginning of what may be the worst mass shooting in Canadian history. When it was over, 14 women had been killed, the gunman had committed suicide, and a dozen other people had been rushed to hospital operating rooms. Based on police and eyewitness accounts, the drama began as students were ending their last classes of the term. About 4:30 p.m., a man thought to be in his twenties and dressed in hunting garb entered the cafeteria on the first floor of the university's engineering building and opened fire with what police believe was a .22 - caliber rifle, killing three The gunman then went up to the second floor and walked into a packed classroom, where he ordered the men into one corner of the room and the women into another. Several of the students, who had been making oral presentations on the final day of classes before exams, said later they thought it was a joke. But the gunman fired a shot into the wall, and they quickly followed his instructions. He told the men to leave. They did so, and police said the gunman screamed before opening fire on the women: `` You're all a bunch of feminists.'' Six slain women were later found in the classroom. On the same floor, he killed a woman in an administration office. Then he climbed to the third floor, where he shot four more women in the corridor. `` It was a human hunt and we were the quarry,'' said one witness quoted by Canadian Press. `` He was clearly gunning for the women,'' said another student. He continued up to the fourth and fifth floors, shooting and wounding both men and women. Then, police say, he returned to the third floor and turned the gun on himself. One police officer who was called to the scene discovered his daughter was among the dead.
