ruso </PERSON>, who was never criminally charged in the murders, also invoked the Fifth Amendment 75 times during his testimony earlier in the lawsuit trial. In testimony shown Wednesday for a 1986 deposition session, <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> admitted four Philippine intelligence agencies operated in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> during his martial-law regime, but he denied they would have used strong-arm tactics. He said he did n't become concerned about anti-Marcos opposition in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> until about 1984.
