<HEAD>Plans Restructuring To Eliminate 1,000 Jobs, Take Writedown</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SKIP WOLLENBERG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Publishing and information services giant <ORGANIZATION> McGraw-Hill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> is trimming more than 1,000 jobs, or 7 percent of its full-time positions, and taking a big charge against its earnings in a cost-cutting realignment. But Wall Streeters sent the company's stock lower Wednesday in what analysts said reflected disappointment with the company's earnings projections for 1990 despite the cutbacks In <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading, <ORGANIZATION> McGraw-Hill </ORGANIZATION> closed down $ 2 a share at $ 61.50. Chairman <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Dionne </PERSON> said next year's earnings, excluding non-recurring gains, would be within a range of $ 3.50 to $ 4 a share even after the the job eliminations and $ 152 million in charges after taxes in the fourth quarter. Last year, <ORGANIZATION> McGraw-Hill </ORGANIZATION> earned $ 3.83 a share. <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Thorp </PERSON>, a media analyst for <ORGANIZATION> Provident </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>, called the cost-cutting move `` one of the more decisive things'' <ORGANIZATION> McGraw-Hill </ORGANIZATION> has done. But he said the earnings projection surprised analysts. `` It's a sign that business is n't really good,'' he said. <PERSON> Bert </PERSON> <PERSON> Boksen </PERSON>, who follows <ORGANIZATION> McGraw-Hill </ORGANIZATION> for <ORGANIZATION> Raymond </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> James </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associates </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Petersburg </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, said, `` The outlook was a lot worse than anybody expected. `` It indicates a softer-than-expected outlook for the school publishing business and a general slowing of the economy,'' he said. The company did not specify where the job eliminations would be, but indicated many would be corporate positions rather than in operating units, which include <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Week </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> magazine </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Poor's debt rating service. `` The effort to improve productivity and make the organization leaner is a step in the right direction,'' said <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Appert </PERSON>, a media analyst for <PERSON> C.J </PERSON>. <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Morgan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grenfell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. But he said the company should do more. `` Operating margins in some of their units are low by industry standards,'' <PERSON> Appert </PERSON> said, citing TV station operations and some information services units. He said the stock market's negative reaction to the announcement would do nothing to discourage speculation that the company may be a takeover target. <ORGANIZATION> McGraw-Hill </ORGANIZATION> said it would deduct $ 220 million from its pre-tax earnings, or $ 152 million after taxes, in the fourth quarter for writing down the value of assets, including those at its DRI-McGraw-Hill economic forecasting unit. The charge also reflects the closing of a unit that publishes general-interest books and the establishment of a reserve for employee severance payments. Several publishing companies recently have taken writedowns, including <ORGANIZATION> Harcourt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jovanovich </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORG