TION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> reports on the construction industry and from corporate staff reductions, spokesman <PERSON> Stewart </PERSON> <PERSON> Trisler </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> McGraw-Hill </ORGANIZATION> employs about 13,700 people, meaning the reductions would amount to a 7 percent cut in staffing. The company earned $ 54.97 million, or $ 1.13 a share, on revenue of $ 507.4 million in the fourth quarter of 1988. It earned $ 185.5 million, or $ 3.83 a share, on revenue of $ 1.82 billion for all of 1988.
