</PERSON> <PERSON> Walker </PERSON>, however, emphasized that the airline was matching the MaxSaver hikes only in selected markets. Passenger traffic normally increases this time of year, a peak travel season. The airlines have been under pressure to hike fares because their costs, mainly fuel prices, have increased sharply in recent months. `` I do n't think it was too much of a surprise, given the way costs have been escalating,'' said <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Starkman </PERSON>, an airline analyst at <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Two weeks ago, a number of big carriers led by <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> said they planned to raise fares on most domestic routes and eliminate discount fares used mainly by business travelers The increases did n't apply to the MaxSavers, however. The airlines said Wednesday they are waiving the usual 14-day advance-purchase requirements for travel between Dec. 20 and Jan. 5 when seats are available. No refunds are allowed, and passengers must buy tickets within 24 hours of making a reservation and must stay over a Saturday night.
