d the <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Technologies </ORGANIZATION> sale had been under consideration for some time. `` We've had some informal inquiries,'' said spokesman <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Harris </PERSON>. `` But we've never had any firm offers.'' <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Iacocca </PERSON> said the vehicle market is going to be fiercely competitive in the future. `` We intend to go head-to-head with the Toyotas and Hondas of the world as well as anybody else in the market,'' he said. `` And this is the right time to take this step. `` The only way to succeed in this kind of environment is to concentrate all our energies and resources on the task of satisfying our customers and insuring that our dealers have the best line of cars and trucks we can possibly produce,'' <PERSON> Iacocca </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> shares rose 12 -LCB- cents to close at $ 19.12 -LCB- a share Wednesday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. Although <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Technologies </ORGANIZATION> accounted for a relatively small chunk of the parent company's overall earnings, analysts said the businesses had been acquired as a way of helping diversify from the cyclical auto industry. <PERSON> Harris </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Technologies </ORGANIZATION> had about $ 149 million in pre-tax profits last year and the company had projected earnings of about $ 121 million this year. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> had after-tax profits of $ 1.05 billion in 1988. The company said the hoped-for sale was unrelated to cash needs, but analyst <PERSON> Kathleen </PERSON> <PERSON> Heaney </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Nikko </ORGANIZATION> <ORGA