<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 216,437 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's 208,977, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in which 263,042 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 130,655 cars this week, compared with 128,866 a week ago and 167,477 in the same week in 1988. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 85,782, compared with last week's 80,111 and last year's 95,565. Canadian automakers were to build 24,670 cars this week, up from 22,798 a week ago and up from last year's 17,866. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,048, compared with 19,340 a week ago and 21,705 in the same week last year.
