<HEAD>Pennzoil Uses Texaco Settlement To Buy Chevron Stake</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Leads with 9 grafs to CORRECT that Pennzoil not considering
buying up to 18 percent of Chevron stock; CORRECT stock price; ADD analyst
comment; picks up 7th graf, However, Ron ...; SUBS last graf to add quarterly
revenue.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 By <PERSON> JOHN </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> BOLT </PERSON>
</TEXT>
<NOTE>AP Business Writer</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, using cash won in a lawsuit against <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, revealed Thursday it had purchased $ 2.1 billion worth of stock in <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the nation's fourth largest oil company. <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION>'s purchase amounts to about 8.8 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> said it was considering spending another $ 500 million to buy more <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> stock. That would boost its stake to more than 10 percent and use up all the net proceeds of its payment from <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>. The disclosure came in a letter to shareholders and filings with the federal <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>. `` This position has been acquired as a long-term investment,'' Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> told shareholders. `` <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> has no interest in attempting to take over <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>.'' The company said it analyzed the possibility of buying up to 18 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>'s stock but `` has no current plans or proposals'' to do so. The announcement helped deflate takeover speculation that had surrounded <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> stock dropped $ 5.25 to close at $ 66.75 in composite trading on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> rose 62 -LCB- cents to close at $ 83.25 as some investors speculated that <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> might try to turn the tables and buy <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION>'s stake or even buy all of <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION>. `` The perception by some investors is that <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>'s response will be to turn around and buy <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> to make the problem go away. No one believes for a minute that <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> intends to buy <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>,'' said analyst <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Escott </PERSON> at <ORGANIZATION> Rauscher </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pierce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Refsnes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> investment firm. `` There is n't any way <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION>'s going to come in and take <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> over,'' agreed another analyst, <ORGANIZATION> George </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gaspar </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Robert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> W. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Baird </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Milwaukee </LOCATION>. However, <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Londe </PERSON> with <ORGANIZATION> A.G. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Edwards </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Sons in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION> said the purchase nevertheless could be a good move. `` <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION>'s notorious for being a very astute investor. San Francisco-based <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> declined to comment on the announcement. Only Wednesday, <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> announced a $ 1 billion sale of 14.1 million shares of common stock to an employee stock owner plan that could make any takeover more difficult. The stock, about 5 percent of the company's outstanding shares, was added to 11 percent already held by an employee profit-sharing plan. <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>, which paid $ 13.3 billion to buy <ORGANIZATION> Gulf </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> four years ago, has seen its stock climb in recent weeks on rumors of a possible takeover bid, with <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> mentioned as a likely suitor. Last year, <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> received $ 3 billion in an out-of-court settlement of its lawsuit against <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> over <ORGANIZATION> Getty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in 1984 and observers have been watching closely to see what the company would do with its windfall. <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> had sued <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> claiming <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s 1984 acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> Getty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> interfered with its plans to buy part of <LOCATION> Getty </LOCATION>. In 1985 a <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> jury awarded <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> $ 10.3 billion. <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> appealed but eventually settled with <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> for the smaller amount. `` Over the past several months, your management and board of directors have reviewed numerous business situations in an effort to find an investment opportunity similar to <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION>'s former stake in <ORGANIZATION> Getty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>,'' said the letter signed by <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hugh </PERSON> <PERSON> Liedtke </PERSON> and President <PERSON> Randal </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> McDonald </PERSON>. `` After thorough study, we have concluded that <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> is by far the most appealing company in the entire spectrum and particularly in its peer group.'' Noting <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>'s profitability has not matched its market position, <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> said, `` <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> has demonstrated expertise in dealing with strictly financial affairs. In the past, it has not seemed to focus that expertise on its operational divisions. If it now does so, we believe the results could be pleasantly surprising.'' <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Harper </PERSON> said the company had until the end of 1990 to reinvest the money from <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> to avoid tax liabilities. <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION> said it believed it could provide `` constructive support'' to <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Derr </PERSON>'s plans to improve the company's performance. <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>, rich in oil and gas reserves and a high-performing chemicals unit, had sales in 1988 of $ 28.9 billion, down from $ 29.1 billion in 1987. Earnings last year totaled $ 1.8 billion, or $ 5.17 a share, up about 40 percent from $ 1.3 billion, or $ 3.65 a share. In its latest quarter, <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION>'s earnings edged down to $ 417 million, or $ 1.22 a share, from $ 420 million, or $ 1.23 a share, a year earlier. <ORGANIZATION> Pennzoil </ORGANIZATION>, whose main business is in motor oil and sulphur, reported third quarter income of $ 35.4 million, or 87 cents per share, compared to $ 39.3 million, 93 cents, for the same period a year ago. Revenue rose to $ 644 million in the third quarter compared to $ 617 million in 1988.
